      "subtitle": "L-alfabett Malti — 30 letters",
      "facts": [
        "The Maltese alphabet has 30 letters: 24 consonants and 6 vowels (a, e, i, o, u, ie).",
        "Although ie is two symbols, it counts as one vowel.",
        "Unique Maltese letters: ċ, ġ, ħ, ż, and għ (għ counts as one consonant).",
        "Each letter has a specific sound, and most Maltese words are pronounced just as they are written.",
        "Maltese has a Semitic base with strong influences from Arabic, Italian, and English."
